entries.title: Why top U.S. officials don't want to give Ukraine tanks
entries.description: Despite German efforts to pressure the U.S. into giving Abrams tanks to Ukraine, the Pentagon’s top leaders are against sending them, say three U.S. officials.

entries.title: Zelenskyy thanks U.S. for latest military aid package
entries.description: The Ukrainian president greeted U.S. Senators Lindsey Graham, Richard Blumenthal and Sheldon Whitehouse in Kyiv and thanked both parties for their continued support. “We need something more,” he added, alluding to negotiations with U.S. and European allies over the supply of tanks.

entries.title: Navy SEAL deserter killed in Ukraine, official says
entries.description: Former Navy SEAL Daniel W. Swift was killed in Ukraine on Wednesday, a Navy official told NBC News Friday.

entries.title: U.S. hands Mexico key suspect in 2014 disappearance of 43 college students
entries.description: U.S. authorities handed over a key suspect in the 2014 disappearance of 43 college students to Mexico. The suspect, Alejandro Tenescalco, was a police supervisor.

entries.title: Church of England apologizes for treatment of LGBTQ people
entries.description: The Church of England formally apologized Friday for its treatment of LGBTQ people even as it said that same-sex couples still will not be allowed to marry in its churches.

entries.title: Romanian court extends Andrew Tate’s detention on alleged human trafficking
entries.description: BUCHAREST — Divisive internet personality Andrew Tate, his brother and two other suspects will remain in custody until Feb.

entries.title: Germany hesitant to send tanks to Ukraine as NATO discusses weapon supplies
entries.description: As the war in Ukraine nears its first full year, NATO leaders are meeting in Germany to discuss future weapons supplies to the country while President Zelenskyy is calling on Western allies to boost arms deliveries. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez reports from Kyiv.

entries.title: U.S. tells allies to 'dig deeper' to help Ukraine with military aid
entries.description: U.S. Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin called for more military aid to be given to Kyiv during a meeting of the Ukraine Defense Contact Group at Ramstein Air Base in Germany.

entries.title: Record-breaking 'Toadzilla' discovered in Australia
entries.description: Australian park rangers believe they have stumbled upon a record-breaking giant toad deep in a Queensland rainforest, dubbing it "Toadzilla."

entries.title: Ukraine appeals to the world for help keeping the lights on
entries.description: Can Ukraine keep the lights on? So far Ukraine has managed to keep its power grid operating despite Russian attacks, but it needs help.

entries.title: Historic building burns in Lima after anti-government protests rock Peru
entries.description: A building was on fire in Lima's historic downtown area after clashes between demonstrators and police during a national strike day demanding that President Dina Boluarte resign and return power to her predecessor.

entries.title: Western defense leaders meet amid dissent over tanks for Ukraine
entries.description: Defense leaders gathered at Ramstein Air Base in Germany heard a plea from Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy as they struggled to resolve ongoing dissent over who will provide battle tanks.

entries.title: Fire burns makeshift homes in shadow of Seoul’s skyscrapers
entries.description: A fire destroyed about 60 makeshift homes in a densely packed neighborhood of Seoul, South Korea on Friday.

entries.title: 60 homes destroyed as fire rips through Seoul shanty  town
entries.description: Firefighters battled a blaze that broke out in a shanty town near to the upscale Seoul district of Gangnam. Hundreds of people were evacuated but there were no immediate reports of casualties.

entries.title: Deadly stampede overshadows rare soccer joy in Iraq
entries.description: Iraq won the men's soccer Gulf Cup for the first time since 1988 with a 3-2 victory over Oman on Thursday, but the triumph was marred by a deadly stampede outside the Basra International Stadium.

entries.title: Meet 'Toadzilla' – Australia's record-breaking cane toad
entries.description: Australian park rangers believe they found a record-setting cane toad deep in a rainforest. Unfortunately for "Toadzilla," its size made it a threat the area's ecosystem.

entries.title: Coast Guard monitoring Russian spy ship on patrol off Hawaii
entries.description: A Russian spy ship has been patrolling off the coast of Hawaii but so far has remained in international waters, the Pentagon said Thursday.

entries.title: Sailor survives 24 days at sea with only ketchup and seasonings to eat
entries.description: A sailor from Dominica was rescued by the Colombia’s navy after what he said was a 24-day ordeal in which he only had a bottle of ketchup and spices to eat.

entries.title: New Zealand Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern leaving office
entries.description: New Zealand’s Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern announced she is leaving office eight months before the next election. NBC News’ Andrea Mitchell reports on Ardern’s accomplishments and legacy.
